{
  "text": "In Fig. 2 , we plot P e and P e against \u03b3 s (dB), and compare them considering a binary antipodal constellation, i.e., (\u03b6 0 = 2, \u03b6 1 = 1), a dB spread \u03c3 y = 6 dB, m y = 0 dB, various values of I and different values of LN . As expected, the results first show that the larger I, N , L are, the better the approximation is. The results also indicate that if I decreases then the approximation becomes looser, nevertheless P e keeps a nearly parallel feature with the curve of P e for large SNR per symbol values. This parallel feature is observed for any value of I. For I = 1, c 1 = 1/2 and b 1 = 1, [CITATION_1] , (26) can be re-expressed as",
